questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue where a high-throughput Spring Boot application experiences a gradual slowdown and eventually crashes with a `java.lang.OutOfMemoryError: Metaspace`. A heap dump analysis reveals millions of dynamically generated class definitions resembling `com.sun.proxy.$Proxy` and `org.springframework.cglib.empty.Object$$EnhancerBySpringCGLIB`. The following code snippet shows the core business service handling payments:

java
@Service
public class PaymentService {
    @Autowired
    private ApplicationContext context;

    public void processPayment(PaymentRequest request) {
        // Dynamically create a transactional proxy wrapper for auditing
        ProxyFactory factory = new ProxyFactory(new RealPaymentProcessor());
        factory.addAdvice(new TransactionInterceptor());
        PaymentProcessor processor = (PaymentProcessor) factory.getProxy();
        processor.execute(request);
    }
}
